From Lance Hartmann Subject Re Diamond Stealth Windows problems In article DIERS writes I own a Stealth card from When using the win driver the card and driver work but are not very ALL of the other windows drivers have a number of Shadows remain when windows are erased and text boxes are often All attempts to get help from Diamond have I have called the Tech support and never been able to get past the hold line a toll call in a reasonable time ie Leaving voice mail has not helped The BBS is a joke It always has too many people on to download You cannot even get a file listing it considers that a download I have faxed the tech support All this with no The bottom line is if you are looking for a fast card and want to use it for windows DO NOT get a Diamond Try another vendor I wish I While others here may have had better experiences I too share the sentiments posted Though I have the original Stealth VRAM it is only relatively recent that the Windows drivers for this card have evolved to a point of decent Note that there are STILL a couple of modes I cannot use will not due to shadowing mis drawn check boxes I believe the version I have is If there's a more recent release I'd appreciate if someone would drop me a note to let me know I haven't been able to get on their BBS lately to check Naturally Diamond doesn't even bother notifying me of fixes Diamond was helpful when I finally reached the right person in curing some of my Windows' problems due to an address The conflicting addresses were OMITTED in at least my version of the Diamond VRAM I hope it has been corrected by The tech rep explained that ALL based boards use these I have not confirmed the validity of that When I upgrade my motherboard in the near future hopefully with some form of local bus I'll seek a video solution from someone other than Lance Hartmann lance Yes that IS a ' ' percent sign in my network All statements comments opinions herein reflect those of the author and shall NOT be misconstrued as